Dress Code Reminders!
We‚Äôre seeing a few things that need to be discussed. We‚Äôve been out a long time, so you might have forgotten.
1. Pants- no tears, holes, rips
2. Shorts- length approaching knees; We don‚Äôt want to measure. Please check at home. No holes, Rips, or tears.
3. Leggings- can be worn under a dress, skirt, or long top.
4. Shirts- no tank tops or spaghetti straps. No exposed skin when arms are raised or when sitting.
5. Shoes- must have a back strap. No flip flops or slides. Crocs must have a back strap.
If you have questions, the complete dress code is in the student handbook on the MISD website, or you can pick up a copy in the office.

post_text:
Return to School Survey

School districts across Texas are struggling to answer one question: What will school be like next year because of COVID-19? We miss the face to face interaction with our students. Our aim is to reopen and allow students to attend classes on campus.

The first day of school is scheduled for August 12th. Please respond to this survey to help us plan for possible options.

By responding to this survey you are not committing to anything. Circumstances may change: however, sharing your thoughts is greatly appreciated. All submissions are anonymous.

Thank you very much for your time and support.

https://www.surveymonkey.com/r/2N3NPRF

MISD would like to introduce you to our newest Mildred Eagle. Please help us give her a warm welcome into eagle country.

Shelly Dyer was recently approved as the Mildred Elementary Principal. Mrs. Dyer has served as Assistant Principal at Fannin Elementary in Corsicana for three years and as an elementary teacher for 20 years. She is married to Shannon Dyer and has two sons Mason (18) and Clayton(14). Mrs. Dyer is looking forward to guiding learning in a safe and cheerful environment. Her years of experience partnering with students, staff, and families will be a benefit to Mildred Elementary School.

post_text:
Monday, April 13, MISD Elementary will distribute one packet per student that will contain work for the remainder of the school year.

To reduce handling of material and possible exposure to Covid-19, we will no longer have Monday pick-ups/drop-offs.

Completed work drop-offs will now be replaced with the use of grade level newspaper stands that will be available to return work at your own convenience. We expect work to be returned in a timely fashion, but the time frame you choose to return the work will be up to you.

Grade level stands will be located under the car rider awning. Please make sure all work is labeled with the name of the student when you return work.

Teachers will still be available weekly for questions and assistance with assignments and work.
text:
Monday, April 13, MISD Elementary will distribute one packet per student that will contain work for the remainder of the school year.

To reduce handling of material and possible exposure to Covid-19, we will no longer have Monday pick-ups/drop-offs.

Completed work drop-offs will now be replaced with the use of grade level newspaper stands that will be available to return work at your own convenience. We expect work to be returned in a timely fashion, but the time frame you choose to return the work will be up to you.

Grade level stands will be located under the car rider awning. Please make sure all work is labeled with the name of the student when you return work.

Teachers will still be available weekly for questions and assistance with assignments and work.

After careful consideration of the current Coronavirus information provided by the State of Texas, MISD will be closed March 16-20. At this time, school will resume on Monday, March 23. All school related events will be canceled. The University Interscholastic League has suspended all UIL sanctioned contests through March 29. Please know the health and well-being of our staff and students is of the utmost importance.

This situation is changing rapidly and we are receiving daily updates from Texas Education Agency. Please be prepared to be flexible as new information becomes available.

Shannon Baker
Mildred ISD

post_text:
Mildred ISD places student safety as its highest priority.
A student recently alerted district personnel of a potential threat written in a textbook. The Navarro County Sheriff‚Äôs Office along with Administration have been investigating the threat and believe it to be non-credible. MISD will take every possible threat seriously and will conduct a thorough investigation. While we don‚Äôt anticipate or believe there is any threat to students and staff at MISD, but erring on the side of caution, MISD will have extra personnel and security at the school tomorrow. We encourage parents to speak with their children to see if they have any information regarding the possible threat. This is an ongoing investigation. Anyone with information is encouraged to contact the Navarro County Sheriffs Department.
Shannon Baker
Superintendent of Schools

Hi Everyone,

Just a reminder that our Zombie 5K run/walk is THIS Saturday at IOOF Park and is open to all interested. Check-in will begin at 10am and the race should begin by 11. Check out the link below to pre-register for only $20 (due at the event), or check-in the day of the event for $25. There will be multiple awards given out for all age groups!

Children under 10 years old can participate for free if accompanied by an adult.

Hope to see you there!

Website: https://mildredband.wixsite.com/mysite
